            <h5>Data Protection</h5>
            <h6>1. General</h6>
            <p>This data protection declaration explains the type, scope and purpose of the processing of personal data (hereinafter referred to as "data") within our online offer and the websites, functions and content associated with it, as well as external online presences, such as our social media profile (hereinafter referred to as collectively referred to as the "Online Offering"). With regard to the terms used, such as "processing" or "person responsible", we refer to the definitions in Article 4 of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).</p>
            <h6>2. Protection of personal data</h6>
            <p>We (FindMyHome.at GmbH, FN 254125p) process your personal data only if you give your consent or to carry out the mandate/request or order you have given for the purposes agreed with you or if there is another legal basis (in the sense of the DSGVO) present. Only such personal data are collected that are necessary for the implementation and processing of our tasks and services or that you have made available to us voluntarily. We only process further personal data if you have voluntarily made your personal data available to us, for example if you contact us. In such a case, we use your personal data to process your requests,Personal data is information by which a person can be clearly identified. This includes the name, e-mail address and telephone number as well as the user's IP address and, if applicable, their domain name or the name of your internet service provider.</p>
            
            <h6>3. Your right to information and deletion (rights of data subjects)</h6>
            <p>You have the right to information about your stored personal data, its origin and recipient and the purpose of the data processing as well as a right to correction, objection, data transfer, restriction of processing and blocking or deletion of incorrect / inadmissibly processed data. You also have the right to revoke any consent you may have given to the use of your personal data at any time. To assert your rights as a data subject (information, deletion, correction, objection and/or data transfer), please contact datenschutz@findmyhome.at.If you are of the opinion that the processing of your personal data by us violates the applicable data protection law or your data protection claims have been violated in some other way, you have the option of complaining to the responsible supervisory authority. In Austria, this is the data protection authority.</p>
            <h6>4. Use of Data - Security</h6>
            <p>We are a real estate platform and therefore we also arrange contacts between interested parties, real estate providers, brokers and cooperation partners. These are moving companies, financing service providers, providers of Internet, TV and landline telephony services as well as mobile phone service providers, providers of neighborhood checks, broker experts for the sale of real estate and other service providers in the field of "everything to do with living". Therefore, certain personal data, which the users of our real estate platform need in order to get in business contact with each other, is passed on (as well as stored, processed and/or transmitted). This is the data and information which are to be stated in connection with the use of our services and or information voluntarily provided by you. The data made available to us will not be processed for purposes other than the purposes set out by use or by consent or by a provision in accordance with the GDPR. Excluded from this is the use for statistical purposes, provided that the data provided has been made anonymous. In any case, the processing also takes place to check and enforce our possible claims/premiums. If we intend to further process your data for another purpose, we will provide you with information about this other purpose and all other relevant information according to Art. 13 Para. 2 DSGVO before this further processing. As part of our quality program, brokers and providers are assessed by our users to improve quality and provide guidance. For this purpose, an evaluation by the user to assess the services of the brokers and providers is collected or obtained by e-mail. The brokers and providers have agreed to participate in the quality program. The submission of a rating by the user is voluntary. The processing of this data takes place exclusively within the framework of the quality program. We have taken state-of-the-art organizational and technical precautions to ensure the protection of your personal data (protection against misuse both internally and externally (e.g. through firewalls, encryption, access authorization, etc.). However, it cannot be ruled out that errors in data transmission not caused by us or unauthorized access by third parties (hackers, etc.) may cause information to be viewed or used by other people. We assume no liability for this, unless this improper use was caused by our fault. Of course, there is the possibility of using or sending very sensitive data or information by post, since absolute security of the e-mail cannot be achieved. unless this improper use was caused by us culpably. Of course, there is the possibility of using or sending very sensitive data or information by post, since absolute security of the e-mail cannot be achieved. unless this improper use was caused by us culpably. Of course, there is the possibility of using or sending very sensitive data or information by post, since absolute security of the e-mail cannot be achieved.</p>
            <h6>5. Weitergabe von Daten an Dritte (Ãœbermittlung)</h6>
            <p>Except in the cases mentioned under point 4, we do not make your personal data available to others. However, in order to fulfill your order or for legal reasons, it is necessary to pass on your data to third parties. These can be courts or authorities or other third parties involved. Third parties are also contract processors (IT consultants, external software partners and data suppliers or processors) who work for us, whereby this is only done to the smallest extent necessary and insofar as it is necessary for the further processing of your request and use. In this case, your data will only be passed on on the basis of the GDPR (based on your consent, fulfillment of a contract, fulfillment of a legal obligation, etc.). We also point out that we may transmit your personal data to recipients (see above) outside your country. However, we transmit your personal data only and exclusively on the basis of the GDPR (appropriate level of data protection or taking measures to ensure that all recipients have an appropriate level of data protection).</p>
            <h6>6. Saving/Deleting Data</h6>
            <p>The data processed by us will be deleted or their processing restricted in accordance with Art. 17 and 18 GDPR. Unless expressly stated in this data protection declaration, the data stored by us will be deleted as soon as they are no longer required for their intended purpose and the deletion does not conflict with any statutory storage requirements. If the data is not deleted because it is required for other and legally permissible purposes, its processing will be restricted. This means that the data will be blocked and not processed for other purposes. This applies, for example, to data that must be retained for commercial or tax reasons.</p>
            <h6>7.Cookies</h6>
            <p>Our website uses cookies. In order to be able to offer you all services in full, to improve your user experience, to improve our quality and our offer, the use of cookies is necessary. "Cookies" are small text files that are stored on the user's device. Different information can be stored within the cookies. A cookie is primarily used to store information about a user (or the device on which the cookie is stored) during or after their visit to an online offer. Temporary cookies, or "session cookies" or "transient cookies", are cookies that are deleted after a user leaves an online offer and closes his browser. In such a cookie z. B. a login status can be saved. "Permanent" or "persistent" refers to cookies that remain stored even after the browser is closed. For example, the login status can be saved if users visit it after several days. The interests of the users can also be stored in such a cookie, which are used for range measurement or marketing purposes. "Third-party cookies" are cookies that are offered by providers other than the person responsible for operating the online offer (otherwise, if they are only their cookies, we speak of "first-party cookies"). which remain stored even after the browser is closed. For example, the login status can be saved if users visit it after several days. The interests of the users can also be stored in such a cookie, which are used for range measurement or marketing purposes. "Third-party cookies" are cookies that are offered by providers other than the person responsible for operating the online offer (otherwise, if they are only their cookies, we speak of "first-party cookies").</p>
            <p>which remain stored even after the browser is closed. For example, the login status can be saved if users visit it after several days. The interests of the users can also be stored in such a cookie, which are used for range measurement or marketing purposes. "Third-party cookies" are cookies that are offered by providers other than the person responsible for operating the online offer (otherwise, if they are only their cookies, we speak of "first-party cookies").We can use temporary and permanent cookies and explain this in our data protection declaration. If you do not want cookies to be stored on your computer, you can deactivate the corresponding option in the system settings of your browser. Saved cookies can be deleted in the system settings of the browser. The exclusion of cookies can lead to restrictions in the function and user experience of this online offer. A general objection to the use of cookies used for online marketing purposes can be raised for a large number of services, especially in the case of tracking, via the US website <a class="a_color text-decoration-underline" href="#">https://www.aboutads.info/choices/</a> or the EU website <a class="a_color text-decoration-underline" href="#">https://www.youronlinechoices.com/</a>be explained. Furthermore, the storage of cookies can be achieved by switching them off in the browser settings. Please note that in this case not all functions of this online offer can be used.</p>
            <h6>8. Web analysis/server log files</h6>
            <p>We, or our hosting provider, collect data about every access to the server on which this service is located (so-called server log files) on the basis of our legitimate interests within the meaning of Article 6 Paragraph 1 lit. The access data includes the name of the accessed website, file, date and time of access, amount of data transferred, notification of successful access, browser type and version, the user's operating system, referrer URL (the previously visited page), IP address and the requesting provider . Log file information is stored for security reasons (e.g. to investigate misuse or fraud) and to optimize the website in terms of user-friendliness and to provide useful information about our services.</p>
